assessment_comment: MOT Chris Highway structure Road ID 3751. Major structure.    Incredible spawning and rearing habitat upstream. Massive outlet pool with erosion indicates cover is extremely under sized.               Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 3751. 10:54:33

Small stream, overgrown with vegetation in sections. Pipenis plastic. Some gravels present, moderate flow. Rail crossing just upstream that appears passable. Downstream crossings on private property. 11:30:44
Nice stream with good flow. Railway crossings approximately 30 m upstream are much more of a barrier then the crossing on Penny Street.           11:19:24

Chinook confirmed upstream in 2018. Structure goes under highway and railway. Culvert visible at inlet but outlet has different structure. Slope estimated. Small step at outlet creating drop.  Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1994444. 17:35:22
No well defined stream channel visible. Flooded wetland area downstream, surveyed during heavy rain. Backwatered pipe.  Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1994950. 16:43:39
Small channel, no outlet drop or pool. Moderate flow, a lot of grassy vegetation on stream banks downstream. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1994901. 15:31:18
Newly installed pipe. Good flow with beaver activity prevalent upstream and downstream. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1994777. 16:14:28

Wide channel, four culverts. Culvert diameter totaled between 4. 2 are in good condition, other two are bent and look older. Railway crossing just upstream, three culverts, appears passable. Abundant gravels present downstream of road. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1994890. 14:48:37

To 1 m pipes on the south side of the railway. It is not clear where the stream crosses under the railway that crossing still needs to be assessed.  Agricultural field located upstream with what appears to be very minimal riparian buffer. Stream has been channelized beside the railway.  A 1 m overflow pipe has been installed above the level of the other 2 pipes.       Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1994680. 18:08:11

Stream dry the time assessment. Flows through agricultural field on both sides. Very minimal willow and cottonwood riparian. Stream is not in maps location. Road embankment is sloughing around the inlet with pipe 50% blocked due to the road fill.           13:20:38

Wetland area upstream. Beaver exclusion cage on inlet. In the cage is completely blocked with material so there is a wetland upstream. Appears to be recent maintenance on the site. Road prism is eroding at the location of the culvert with a piece of pipe set aside that has possibly been recently removed.    Culvert slope estimated as could not see through the pipe.                 12:55:42
Abundant gravels present downstream and upstream. Small fish seen in culvert and downstream. Flow up and downstream but culvert is backwatered.  12:52:51

Predominantly fine substrate in stream bed but abundant gravels upstream as well. Wide channel with good flow. Small debris jam near outlet but does not look like a barrier. Very deep, muddy outlet pool.  12:16:38
Concrete pipe. Smaller stream with some flow. Chinook observations, upstream and downstream of this crossing in FISS.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1994747. 16:28:14
Good flow. Small channel with fine substrate. Pipe is bent up approximately 2 m downstream of the inlet. Debris guard has been built around the inlet.           14:08:24
Beaver grate at inlet, moderate outlet drop and pool. Wetland type habitat upstream. Very turbid stream water. 14:03:23
Small debris jam at outlet causing drop. Culvert is old and warped. Velocity is much higher in pipe than upstream. Predominantly fine substrate upstream, some gravels downstream. 13:30:15

Very nice stream with abundant gravel’s and good flow upstream. Some old growth cedar within the upstream riparian area. Culvert must be bent in the middle because cannot see through. Pipe gradient estimated. Large outlet drop and deep outlet. Pool indicate culvert is extremely undersized.           13:38:13
Fully embedded pipes. Three pipes with two at 1.8 m and one at 1.2 m. Nice habitat, upstream with abundant gravels some deeper pools and deeply undercut banks. 15:31:23

Three pipes at 0.9 m each. Made of concrete and built in 1930. Nice stream with good flow. Abundant rearing habitat located upstream.  Although the stream has a lot of volume, the depth in the one pipe functioning is extremely shallow with a 50 cm concrete drop at the outlet.             11:38:41

Two 0.9m pipes. Nice stream with good flow. There is another culvert located downstream on the driveway to a private residence that has a small outlet drop in approximately 20 cm. Some gravel is upstream of the railway.  No barrel photos. 12:00:42

Two pipes made of concrete under the railway 0.9 m each. Crossing constructed in 1934. Nice stream good flow. Some small gravel’s located upstream. Wire mesh cages attached to inlets upstream - poentially for beaver. Fill depth measured at 12m, but changed to 9.9 to satisfy submission template macros. 12:07:26
Grassy vegetation upstream and downstream, little to no riparian. Runs through private property downstream. Small channel with low flow. 16:11:20

Wide stream, high flow and good habitat. Bridge on railway just upstream. Major moti structure, was in the wrong spot on the map. Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 3626. 11:13:09

Three pipes. Two at 1.2 m and one at 2.0 m in the middle. Both 1.2 m pipes are completely submerged underwater and the 2 m pipe is 100% back watered. Assuming embedded due to the depth of the back watering. Bridge located just upstream on River Road. Crossing underneath the railway still needs to be assessed.           Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 4172. 17:04:42

Stream not present at this location within freshwater atlas. Good flow and abundant, small gravels upstream and downstream. Although pipe appears undersized, the size and depth of the outlet pool indicates that it handles the flow decently well.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1995103. 14:41:27

Steep waterfall 10m downstream of crossing, height approx 8m. Stream gradient and channel width taken upstream. Gravels present upstream, but definite barrier downstream. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1473114. 16:34:20

Could not locate pike as it is underwater at both inlet and outlet. Appears to be a bunch of logs under the road so suspect that there may be no structure at all as the drainage may have been put in with logs - although MOT culvert layer says 0.6 m galvanized pipe.. Road is failing with 3 foot deep and 2 foot wide hole in the road marked with a pilon.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1993428. 14:32:19

Deep canyon and high waterfall directly downstream of crossing. Definite barrier to all fish. Rough estimate 20m height. Outlet drop and pool estimated, unsafe to get near stream due to steep embankment. RB confirmed upstream of crossing.  Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 30367. 17:27:23

Absolutely massive structure with 12 m of fill plus the height of the culvert which appears to be approximately 7 m. Fill depth changed to 9.9 to satisfy submission template macros. Very nice llarge stream with  boulder step pool habitat suitable for bull trout  Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 3691. 17:00:34

Very large system with beaver complex upstream. Large beaver dam approximately 1.3 m high located 25 m upstream of the inlet. Approximately 20 m downstream of the outlet is a rock shoot that is over 30% but only for 5 m with a total height of 1.7 m. There’s significant erosion of the road prism on the upstream side above the culvert. Culvert is located on the bend of Highway 16 under 10 m of fill.  Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992752. 16:16:08

Very big outlet drop, measured to top of substrate but likely underestimated. Gravels present upstream that could be suitable for spawning. Small debris jam ~15m upstream of crossing but likely not a major barrier. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992618. 10:50:45

Culvert is a little backwatered at outlet. Small fish seen in pipe. Trib to major spawning stream. Crossing appears passable. Slight inlet drop due to woody debris. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992616. 11:30:43

Very large low gradient stream with chinook points. Hydro metric station upstream. Outlet drop is comprised of boulders. Likely placed there to aid in passage. At downstream end of powerline Corredor. There is a steep cascade section for approximately 30 m that is 8% gradient.           Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 3749. 12:57:36

Massive outlet drop and deep pool. Drop and pool depth estimated. Signs of beaver activity near inlet. Looks like an old well is attached to inlet side? Water could be flowing through, underneath surface, not visible.  Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992863. 13:34:08

Big wetland upstream. Inlet could not be found, likely submerged. Small channel downstream, pipe looks old and in bad shape. Overflow pipe near first pipe but not functioning currently.  Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992855. 14:06:57

Big beaver dam near inlet of culvert spanning across whole channel, approx 1.2m high. Boulders in pipe near inlet creating small drop and increasing velocity. Channel widens downstream, high value habitat. RB and CCG confirmed upstream and downstream.  Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992674. 14:54:00

Large stream with abundant gravels present upstream suitable for cultural spawning. Massive outlet drop with powerline riparian cleared downstream of the highway.   Old growth cedar hemlock riparian within Sugar bowl grizzly den provincial park. Follow up with habitat confirmation recommended.                 Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992815. 11:30:20

Very nice stream with steeper cobble boulder habitat, potentially valuable rearing for Bulltrout . Very steep and long pipe with transmission line vegetation cleared at outlet.  20 m section of stream di watered approximately 10 m downstream of the outlet due to a graded substrate likely related to highway corridor.    Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992817. 11:05:47

Embedded culvert, high flowing mountain stream. Very clear and wide channel. Gradient increases upstream. Small stream from drainage ditch flowing into inlet. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992808. 11:55:36

Culvert very old. Big wetland complex upstream. Inlet barely visible, covered in woody debris and rusty metal. Culvert slope estimated. High velocity coming out of outlet with moderate drop. Habitat looks good downstream, wide channel with high flow. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992569. 12:49:05

Horse tail and willow wetland upstream with a small well defined channel with fine gradients. Pipe is blocked by beaver debris. There’s a second pipe that’s approximately 1.5 m higher 0.9 m wide that is free of debris and functions as an overflow. Potential refuge area during periods of high flow in a Fraser, which was only 40 m downstream at the time of assessment.          Gate at the end of the road preventing access to launch point for Penny. Consider road deactivation?          Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1993423. 13:44:19

Wetland type habitat, upstream with multiple small channels threaded through it. Inlet of pipe is extremely bent. Nice little stream with well defined channel downstream. Good amount of flow in this stream connected to known chinook system.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1992666. 10:35:14

Very wide stream with high flow. Velocity is high in culvert. Very deep and big outlet pool, depth estimated. Known salmon spawning location. Chinook confirmed downstream in past. Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 3750. 10:13:57

Stream flows into crossing from the east, flowing along the ditch for approximately 60 to 70 m. Very nice stream with good flow abundant gravels and some pools to 50 cm deep. inlet is completely buried as outlet is blocked by beaver debris. Culvert slope estimated.           09:31:27

Wetland lake area upstream with small channels threaded through it. Great on culvert inlet and pipe is in poor shape as it is rusted and bent out of shape. Outlet back water for 40%. Small stream with some flow.           10:14:44

Big wetland area upstream. Smaller, grassy, wetland downstream. RB confirmed upstream in the past. Culvert is very old and in bad shape. There is a bigger, overflow pipe but it's too high above the water and is not functioning.  09:37:55

2 culverts, one bigger than the other. Debris jams at inlet creating drop and increasing stream velocity in pipe. Rail crossing upstream is a concrete OBS. Channel wider downstream than upstream.  11:06:36

Continuously embedded culvert. Agricultural fields upstream and downstream. Very little riparian vegetation. Small fish seen near inlet. Channel looks like it gets smaller upstream, flows through cow field. Not a fish passage issue. But riparian restoration could be pursued.  RB confirmed in the past near crossing. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1473360. 12:54:06
Continuously embedded culvert. Wide channel with moderate flow. High value habitat   10:09:03

Chinook and mountain whitefish confirmed just upstream in 2019. Continuously embedded culvert. Grassy habitat upstream with little riparian on streambanks near crossing. Fines the predominant stream substrate.  09:09:59
Dewatered and no defined stream channel found. Plastic culvert. Flow goes through mainstem of Dominion Creek just north through town. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1462891. 11:52:44

RB and CCG confirmed downstream in past. Private agricultural land upstream and downstream. Embedded culvert. Small wooden dam just downstream of crossing. Approx 0.8m high. Small trickle beside structure that would allow fish to swim upstream.  Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1461195. 12:32:44

Wide channel, high flowing stream. Small outlet drop and high velocity in pipe but likely not a issue for adult salmonids. Chinook confirmed downstream near Fraser confluence in the past. Railway bridge downstream seen in photos. Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 30365. 10:49:31

Wetland habitat upstream and downstream. Crossing is near transmission line, trees have been cut down. Backwatered culvert, pipe appears undersized. Chinook confirmed in the past downstream of crossing. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1473381. 09:43:53

Call vert is also under McClellan Road. Small stream with good flow and primarily fine substrate. extensive beaver activity, both upstream and downstream, with dams of up to 1 1/2 m high in both locations.          very long structure. Culvert gradient estimated as could not see through the pipe.       Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1467210. 11:30:35
Very small stream, low flow with some water present. Embankment above outlet has been covered to prevent rockslide. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1461358. 13:46:10

Small stream with low flow. Muddy, fine substrate makes up most of streambed. Very close to Fraser River. Likely not big enough to be used by adult salmonids. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 3189063. 15:17:53

Stream flows through private fenced off land on both sides. Moderate flow and a wide entrenched channel upstream. It appears cobbles are the predominant stream substrate and gravels subdominant. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1463590. 15:57:40

Large stream with Cabo boulder substrate suitable for both trout. Concrete box culvert is 60% embedded on the downstream side. Decent amount of debris is clogging the inlet.           Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 29885. 15:39:24

Pipes and Rode are in extremely poor condition with evidence of embankment failure and pipes rusted all the way through on the bottom side in places. Small side road parallel to Highway 16 with residences that could be accessed from either side. Removal of crossing could perhaps be considered. Large high value system suitable for bulltrout rearing.  Culvert upstream is relatively new concrete box culvert on the highway which is over half embedded and 3.7m wide. Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1466350. 15:53:19

Nice little stream with good flow and abundant small gravel’s upstream. May be crossings downstream on private land. Quite a bit of large riprap placed around inlet and outlet to protect the crossing. Outlet is placed on large piece of riprap, so 0.3 m was added to the 0.2 m outlet drop to account for the additional distance from the stream to the outlet.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1466467. 14:00:15

Two pipes at 1.4 m diameter each. Crossing is only 5 m downstream of the railway crossing. Stream has far more volume of water at this location than it did below Highway 5. Water may be recharging Beaver influenced wetlands downstream. Road edge has been armoured with riprap and downstream side of road bank is eroding significantly for approximately 60 m.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1468680. 12:14:12

Stream is mostly the water. Large beaver dam (1.7m high) located approximately 30 m upstream. Fully in bedded pipe with beaver. Great on the inlet. On assessed crossing on private driveway upstream from here. Adjacent landowner has concerns about the recent lack of water, and says it is on characteristic for the section of stream. They have concerns that recent pipeline construction, just upstream of this crossing has potentially influenced beaver populations, and water flow. 09:47:05

Newly installed culvert. Beaver influenced wetland area upstream and downstream. Channel width estimated as wetland areas present.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1468490. 09:14:05

Very nice stream with salmon point in FISS located upstream. Very good flow with some pools present to 80 cm deep upstream. Railway crossing, approximately 200 m of stream still needs to be assessed.                   There is no crossing at the pipeline, but construction activities have resulted in a small cascade of boulders at the pipe Crossing location. It is similar to cascade section observed, approximately 50 m upstream.           Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1467202. 12:56:09

Very nice stream with good flow and abundant gravels upstream. Pipe is an extremely bad shape with extensive corrosion inside of the pipe particularly at the downstream and - see photos.  Likely at least one crossing downstream on private land.  Transmission line corridor is located immediately upstream and the channel appears to be modified in this location to be straighter and narrower than its natural state.  No crossing immediately upstream on Goslin Road (no road - crossing should be removed as potential barrier in bcfishpass)            Ministry of Transportation chris_culvert_id: 1465295. 14:28:28

Culvert is undersized for a stream of this size. High flow, just over 10m wide upstream. Chinook confirmed downstream in the past.  Ministry of Transportation chris_hwy_structure_road_id: 29925. 14:39:41

Covert runs under both sets of tracks. Model Crossing will need to be removed from bcfishpass. Outlet of this pipe is immediately upstream of Loseth road with significant armouring around the outlet, pool and road at the inlet downstream. Very nice stream with significant amounts of flow. Known rainbow stream. Much less flow downstream below Highway five, which is very interesting.           12:21:02
